N2  - This paper extends the Sequential Unconstrained Minimization Technique for nonlinear programming to include problems where the constraints are a mixture of inequalities and equalities. Theorems indicating the dual nature of the method and the solution of a subproblem are given. Finally, the theoretical basis for a k-point extrapolation procedure is established.
